{\"rawText\":\"Chapter 1\n\nIt was a dark and stormy night. The rain fell in torrents, and the wind howled through the trees. Captain Ahab stood at the helm of the Pequod, his wooden leg tapping against the deck as he scanned the horizon for the great white whale. This was his obsession, his reason for living. The crew watched him warily, knowing that their captain was driven by a madness that could consume them all.\n\nChapter 2\n\nIshmael sat in the tavern, nursing a tankard of ale as the fire crackled beside him. He had signed on to the Pequod seeking adventure, not realizing that he had boarded a ship destined for tragedy. The old sailors told tales of Moby Dick, the ghostly white whale that had taken Ahab\'s leg, and Ishmael wondered if he had made a terrible mistake.\"}  
